&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;When toxic substances enter water bodies, it causes water pollution&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It can be caused by the&lt;strong&gt; improper use of pesticides&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The water gets contaminated&amp;nbsp;when pesticides used on land areas are flushed away by wind and rainfall into water bodies.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Pesticide&amp;nbsp;alters the state of water bodies by changing to their physical, chemical, or biological conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Various human activities can lead to water pollution.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The emissions from factories and vehicles are released into the air which settles&amp;nbsp;into the water bodies in the form of acid rain.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Industrial waste and sewage water also drain into water bodies when there is no efficient drainage system.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Population growth increases human activities which further expand the water pollution caused by it.&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As population density increases, the waste generated in households ends up in water bodies&lt;/strong&gt; polluting them.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Human activities (washing clothes and utensils)&amp;nbsp;around water bodies increase with the increase in population leading to water pollution. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thus, the reason for water pollution is pesticides, human activity, and population growth.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

